variables.value: Sorry, I was looking around the school\nand lost track of time.
Ah, there you are.\nLet me introduce you to the class.
Let me introduce you to the class.
No need to be nervous—\nI'm sure you'll fit right in.
Hey, <FLC:UNMEI>. Hmm? <FLC:SAKURAZAKI>? Well...\nI believe he used to play football. Back in elementary,\nhe was top of his class—smart, athletic, the whole package.
These days, though, he just puts all that talent into picking fights...\nI want to believe he's still a good kid deep down, but... Yeah.
Even the other eighth grade teachers\ndon't quite know what to make of him.
Oh dear...\nThe words just won't come out right...
Never heard of her...\nAlso, what's a non-council student like you even doing here?
Oh no...\nWhat am I gonna do?!
Oh! Great timing! You there, newcomer!\nYou look like you can keep a secret!\nMind helping me out with something?
Keep this between us, okay? I lost my super-secret Lilac keepsakes!\nYou know, Lilac, the student council president?\nHelp me look for them? Please?
If word gets out I had that stuff, I'm toast!\nThey'd roast me on the school forums, and that'd be it...\nJust thinking about it makes my knees shake...
I'm begging you. You'll help me out, right?
Thank you! I knew I could put my trust in you!
My three keepsakes are scattered across the school grounds. They're about the size of a postcard, so they might've gotten stuck somewhere...
Please find them quickly, before anyone else does!
Tch! Get lost if you're not going to help. Scram!
There are three of them, all about the size\nof a postcard. Easily lost, you see...\nThey could be anywhere on campus...
Please find them quickly, before anyone else does!
Sorry, but I'm no longer in the business. If you want the goods,\nyou'll have to find someone with tougher nerves than me.
I can't stop thinking about it...
But if I were to go now...
Oh, Destin! Perfect! Could you perhaps do me a favor?
I left something in the storage room of the old gymnasium...\nIt'd be a little embarrassing if I were to be seen with\nsomething like that around school, so, uh...
If you can, do you think you could discreetly go and fetch it for me?
Thank you! That would be incredibly helpful. So, what you're looking for...
It's white and has, um... two round, squishy parts on it...\nOh, gosh, this is so embarrassing!
Anyway, you'll know when you see it! Thank you in advance!
Oh, you have plans of your own right now? Sorry about the short notice.\nI guess I'll just have to go for it later, in secret...
It's white and has, um... two round, squishy parts on it...\nOh, gosh, this is so embarrassing!
Anyway, you'll know when you see it!\nThank you in advance!
Ah, <FLC:UNMEI>. You retrieved it for me!\nI knew I could count on you!
It was a gift from my nephew. It, uh... looks a little strange,\nbut... I do kind of like it.
I think the kids call this sort of thing "creepy-cute?" Anyways,\nIf any students found out, they'd surely think I'm weird.\nThanks for fetching it for me.
I think the kids call this sort of thing "creepy-cute?" Anyways,\nIf any students found out, they'd surely think I'm weird.\nThanks for fetching it for me.
Anyone glued to a book probably loves reading.\nI bet they've heard of Sigdor's Tale too.
Heehee... I can't believe there's another Sigdorian here!\nI'm so happy!
I've heard of it... but I'm not really into fantasy,\nso I've never picked it up.
Sigdor's Tale?\nThat's the one that got an anime adaptation, isn't it?
I've got a copy at home, but I didn't bring it today...\nso yeah, not right away. Sorry!
With info that vague, I doubt you could pinpoint any individual.
Today's another beautiful spring day...\nBut why lend an ear to a babbling brook like me?
Boo-yah! I'm <FLA:MAKUSHITA> from the sumo club!\nAiming to be champion in both sumo and football, yo!
I enjoy helping those who give their all.\nBut this time, I want to be a player myself!
A great school life starts with good grooming!\nTime for a dress code check!
I'd love to find a new model for the club...
We won't turn a blind eye just because you're new!\nNow, let's see...
Freshmen like you who are still learning the ropes\noften find themselves right in the middle of a juicy scoop!
Hey, you like manga, right?\nThere's no way you wouldn't!
I'll let it slide this time.\nBut you better show some school pride!
Oh, you're busy? \nLet me know if you're ever free.
...I'll let it slide today.\nBut next time, no excuses!
Dodging questions, huh?\nI'll get the scoop next time!
All I wanted was a little praise...\nI'll show you my next one soon!
I-I'm busy right now, so I'll let this one slide.\nDefinitely NOT because I'm scared or anything!
A footballer? Someone like you?\nJust make sure you don't cause trouble or drag others down.
<FST:SAKURAZAKI>...? <LST:SAKURAZAKI>?! Uh...\nLook, I'm not saying anything bad, just—keep your distance!
You know what they say... Let sleeping dogs lie.
Don't say I didn't warn you.
You know what they say... Let sleeping dogs lie.
Your notoriety might go down in history, huh...
<FLC:SAKURAZAKI>, huh...? With a family like his,\nhe gets away with everything.
If it weren't for their backing, he would've been\nexpelled ages ago. Life's just not fair, is it?
Wh-what do you want? Don't come near me! I have nothing to say to you!
I can't imagine what\ngoes on in his head...
<FLC:SAKURAZAKI>, you say? He's a scary one, all right.\nThankfully, he's a lone wolf who keeps to himself.
In that sense, he's a bit better than the punks\nyou usually see hanging around convenience stores.
You're a peculiar guy, alright.\nA different breed altogether.
Who, <FLC:SAKURAZAKI>? Yeah, don't even think about crossing him.\nTake one of his kicks, and it's lights out, bro.
Gah! You're one of <FLC:SAKURAZAKI>'s goons?!\nPlease, I didn't see nothin'!
He was all hyped to go delinquent for his middle school debut...\nbut <FUL:SAKURAZAKI> crushed that dream real quick.
Sorry about him, he saw <FLC:SAKURAZAKI> kick a ball once\nand it apparently brought back some bad memories...
<FLC:SAKURAZAKI>? Ahh, the rowdy type you see all the time in schools.\nThough, I can tell there's more to him than meets the eye.
He's got a gift in those legs of his, no doubt.\nShame he wastes that talent brawling, instead of doing something greater.
Speaking of five years ago... just before it happened,\nthere was quite a stir about a new facility being constructed.
And not just the school.\nThe whole town was talking about it.
The old football club, huh? They had a solid reputation.\nMost of the members were kind and easygoing.
They couldn't turn their backs on anyone in need.\nThat's the kind of people they were.
I heard this from my sister,\nbut the school's reputation really took a hit because of the incident.
They tried to do damage control\nby disbanding the football club.
At the time, neither side would back down\nand things were really heating up...
It's unfortunate what happened to the football club,\nbut at least the faction feud ended when it all settled.
The key to the Archive? Not in the key rack?\nThen I have no idea where it could be.
The art club manages its keys properly.\nWe always return them to the staff room right after use!
None of our members have gone into the Archive recently,\nas we haven't had any need to reference historical records.
I know it's not our school, but...
Feels a little too\nperfect, doesn't it?
People are saying some giant <FUL:UMIBOZU> showed up on campus.\nLike... really?
Okay, sure, the football club's popular.\nI'm still not getting involved in your scheme.
<FLC:SAKURAZAKI> feels different lately. Like, his whole vibe's softer?
My friend's school barely has any students left.\nKinda lucky ours is fine.
The high schoolers are really moving out...?\nI'm still not used to the name Southcrest High.
So the football club gets to stay in Odaiba?\nThat's basically a vacation!
Hey, you know <FUL:KAMEO>? Seventh grader, kinda turtle-y?\nI saw him with this drop-dead gorgeous girl!
Grand finals...? Wait, they're actually good?
Lots of people are claiming they saw it attack a student.
Football sounds cool and all, but I'm awful at sports, so... sorry.
Now that the club's back, maybe <FLC:SAKURAZAKI> will stop picking fights too.
If their school shut down... would that mean vacation forever?
You think the Northbright kids can even keep up here?
The Odaiba Football Gardens sound amazing.
Wait! Is that his girlfriend...?! Wild.\nNever judge a person by their looks, huh?
If someone's behind all this, my money's on <FLC:UNMEI>.
So those guys\nmade it through, huh.
Bet it was all\nthe captain's call.
I mentioned the big match and <LST:SEKOTA> just started chewing me out.\nTotal hypocrite. He never says jack to the baseball team...
That many people applied and only fifteen got interviews?\nBrutal, man...
Can I get one that\ndoes my homework?
That team's way stronger\nthan West Manor.
They're willing to\ndo whatever it takes.
You really turned away <FUL:GARYU>?\nThat was a bold move...
You're quite the hot topic online.\nNever thought football would actually make a comeback...
To win over all those big-name students this fast...\n<FLC:UNMEI>'s got an incredible power to unify people.\nTo be frank, it's downright terrifying.
You won the first match, just like that?\nAnd against <FUL:HARU>, no less!
A good manager can make or break a team.\nIf we get a new one from the merger,\nWho knows how the team will change...?
The football club went from zero to Grand Finals\nin the blink of an eye. Things are going well...\nAlmost too well, no?
Royal Academy's next, right? They're insanely strong...\nBut, uh, even if our club loses, they've come really far.
Even without <FUL:HARU>, Raimon's still tough.\nWinning it all... that might be too much. No offense.
I just saw <FLC:SENNO> head into the council room...\nShe's so elegant—even from behind...!
I wanna be on the student council... No, <FLC:SENNO>'s personal ninja!\nI'd obey her every command... even if it meant death!
She had that serious, broody look on her face...\nEven that's gorgeous on her. But still... I'm worried.
Guess they called off\nthe PTA meeting.
The baseball faction drama? Complaints have stopped cold.\nBut I'm all for <FLC:SENNO> having one less thing on her plate.
She's pulling double duty: council and football club.\nShe's just got that natural talent for leading people... sigh...
<FLC:SENNO>'s off with the football team, so I knew I wouldn't find her here...\nbut my feet brought me to the council room anyway.
The ones still in the council are really busting their butts...\nThat football club totally stole all their best members!
If the football club wins, that's <FLC:SENNO>'s win!\nSo you'd better take that championship...\nor I'll hold a grudge forever.
Made it to the semis, so yeah.
The baseball club's scary, but <FLC:SAKURAZAKI>? Way worse.\nSo yeah, I'm with you guys.
Wha—<FLC:SAKURAZAKI>?! D-Did I do something wrong?!
Man, you're lucky, <FLC:UNMEI>. I wanna be one of <FLC:SAKURAZAKI>'s lackeys too!
<FUL:JINNAI> from Northbright. He grew up in a family of delinquents!\nHe's got that raw street vibe, y'know?\nDifferent from <FLC:SAKURAZAKI>, but just as cool.
I'mma hold the fort while <FLC:SAKURAZAKI>'s away!\nI'll keep a close eye out for any funny business.
Even the out-of-school punks are catching the football bug.\nI saw some rough-lookin' dudes kicking a ball around in an alley.
The Football Frontier's huge!\nEven this sketchy guy I ran into said he's tuning in for the finals!
This guy talks big like he's some bad boy, but he's actually a total coward.\nWish he had half your guts.
Uh... p-please don't stare like that...\nI'm begging you.
This guy used to be scared stiff of <FLC:SAKURAZAKI>,\nbut now he's head over heels after seeing him play.\nKeeps saying he wants to be one of his underlings.
<FUL:SAKURAZAKI>, <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>... <FUL:JINNAI>, Northbright...\nHonestly, those two are way more intense than the Street Howlers gang.
He always gets carried away, that's just his style.\nI wish he had even half of <FLC:SAKURAZAKI>'s chill.
He's super easy to influence, y'know?\nEven if he begs to join the club, don't take it too seriously.
Some thug jumped him for glaring at him too hard,\nbut then he brought up the Football Frontier\nand they totally hit it off.
Seeing a football makes me want to kick one around.\n...Ah right, oops. Scratch that.
Make sure you finish up any studying before the bell rings.
You're a hot topic even amongst the teachers.\n"The newbie making waves," they're saying. Hahaha.
Aww, man... never thought I'd miss the bus...
I cut it a bit close today, but after dashing up the Hecaton\nevery day for two years, I'd say I've gotten pretty fast.
I was only late because the bus was slow.\nWish I had something faster, like a private jet or something.
I just wanted to check the school socials before bed,\nbut I couldn't put my phone down... I totally overslept.
All those last-second sprints have really built up my speed.\nFootball club, maybe? Then again, a latecomer probably won't cut it.
No way a teacher has\nthat kinda hobby...
Oh, you're a freshman? This spot has just the right amount\nof background noise to help me concentrate while reading.
Have you heard of Sigdor's Tale?\nI want to read it, but it's not in our library.
Last year, I couldn't decide between the space laboratory\nand the stargazing club. I ended up joining neither.
I saw your football match the other day\nand found it really interesting.\nI'm learning the rules so I can enjoy it more.
I've got a better grasp of football now after studying up.\nI'd like to watch a match with Keshin sometime.
Whether it's friends or rivals, knowing yourself\nand your opponent is what really matters.\nThat's how you win.
I'm eager to see how your match turns out.\nEven a bookworm like me might have to bookmark the finals.
The dance club\nis on point today!
I'm short on sleep from trying to catch up with my studies.\nBut if I doze off during class, I'll fall behind even more...
I was napping, so I missed it...\nWell, I could care less...
I'm always up past midnight trying to finish everything...\nThen I get to school and totally crash...
I always end up nodding off in <FUL:KASUMIN>'s class.\nHer voice is just so soothing, I just...
I think the secret to a healthy life is doing everything in moderation.
You are such a sleepyhead...\nSleep more, you're still growing!
If you get up early to study, it's a win-win!\nThings get even tougher in high school,\nso you need to fix your habits now!
I wonder what kind of stuff they've got stored on the third floor.\nIf there's anything useful for students,\nthey should just let us see it!
Come on, girl... You're already bad at math.\nWhat'll you do if even Miss <LST:KASUMISAKI> gives up on you?!
Bet it'll be one\nfor the books.
You don't look too happy... Are you okay?\nMust be tough adjusting to a new place.
The school app? That was made by the computer club!\nThe president put so much love into every detail.
I saw <FLC:SAKURAZAKI> down at the Shopping District.\nHe seemed to be getting along well with the noodle shop lady.
If the football club's back,\nthat means that whole incident is over, right?\nNot sure what happened... But hey, good for you!
Merging with a school we literally just fought in a match?\nAwkward much?
You're going all the way to Tokyo. Might as well enjoy it!\nYou can go shopping, sightseeing, the whole shebang.\nLive a little!
Even the teams that lost are still hanging around\nthe Football Gardens, right?\nHope they get to make some fun memories with them too.
Even the teachers are fidgety these days.\nMine goofed up the board like, three times in one class.
Have you seen some of the schools our graduate class went on to?\nWe have to study hard so we don't lose to them!
I heard they take on any app request, big or small...\nKinda worried they're swamped.
People at the Shopping District were talking about you, <FLC:UNMEI>.\nAre you famous now or what?
Eighth grade's the prime time to shine in a club.\nSticking with football? They must really be into it.
I had a friend at Northbright back in grade school.\nNever thought we'd be classmates again like this!
Big cities and crowds aren't really my thing.\nYou guys try not to get lost out there, okay?
Watching them makes me feel super out of shape...\nMaybe I should start working out or something.
Some stores in the Shopping District\nare closing just to watch the grand final.\nYou guys really are kind of a big deal.
If only I could get\na recommendation...
I wonder if my grades\nare good enough...
You've still got time\nto bounce back.
I might have to\nretake the test...
Hey, why the long face?\nDon't tell me you failed too...?
How do I use this thing?
I never imagined the day would come when we'd teach with tablets.\nThe march of technology is just amazing...
Ah, <FLC:SAKURAZAKI>. I'm always grateful for your father's support.\nPlease give him my thanks, would you?
<FLC:MOMOCHI> showed me this mechanical thing called a "drone,"\nand goodness, I thought she'd caught a UFO!
I had a chance to chat with the teachers from Northbright,\nand they showed me how to teach with digital tools.\nIt was very educational.
...Ah, hello <FLC:UNMEI>. Good luck with your match against Northbright.
This merger really came out of the blue.\nAll the Northbright students are lovely, though.
Apparently someone's posting updates about <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> online,\nbut I can't for the life of me remember their username...
Gaaah... I've collected so much data that I can't manage it all.\nI'm being squashed by numbers!
I'll be sure to check out the match broadcast too!\n...Erm, now how do I do that again?
Gagh-hagh...! Hmm...? You're looking worse for wear...\nHit me up if you're gonna come to the infirmary.\nI'm there quite often, you see.
You've been slacking off\na lot lately.
I can't help wanting to watch the baseball club's show\non the school grounds.
I'll finish reading all\nof them before graduation!
I'm picky about books, but <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>\nhas a surprisingly solid collection. I'm impressed!
Have you ever watched a movie adaptation and suddenly wanted\nto read the original? That's why my to-read list never ends.
Looks like there still aren't many football books around.\nNobody's against it now, so maybe I'll donate a few.
The way they describe\nthe goddess's power...
I love how massive\nthe scale feels.
I might donate a few of my favorite fantasy novels too.\nYou'll never forget 'em, even after just one read.
I wonder which club would\nmake me the most popular...
We're going to try all the best food\n<MNT:NAGUMOHARA> has to offer!
If we start a Gourmet Club, we can use the club budget\nto eat our way through <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>!
Hey, help me stop this guy. If he starts a club just to feed himself,\nhe'll be stuck in detention till the sun blows up...
How about you just take\nit easy at home today?
Like I said,\njust take it easy.
How long are you\ngonna keep this up...
Do I look like\nI'm faking it?
Not something you\nshould get used to...
Hey, there. Isn't our campus just beautiful?\nIf I didn't have a stomachache, I'd offer to show you around.
Hey, you. I saw your hijinks, and now I can't stop shaking.\nMy stomach's been in knots too.
I heard the student council's thinking of using force,\nbut I can't picture <FLC:YAJIMA> and <FLC:GOSAKI> actually throwing punches.
I missed the dance battle the other day as my stomach was acting up...\nBut I have to be better in time to see you take on the baseball team!
Football's finally gotten its dignity back.\nNow if only I could reclaim my right to a pain-free stomach...
<FLC:SAKURAZAKI> and <FLC:RAIKA> can't seem to get along.\nI for one wouldn't have the guts to break up a fight between\nthose two...
So many new students all at once.\nI'm so nervous, my palms are sweaty!
You're in a big tourney, right? Just hearing that makes me nervous.\nYou don't seem fazed, though.
Look after yourself out there. Your opponents in the semifinals\nlook super scary. I think I'd get KO'd in a heartbeat...
This is it. The end. Just thinking about it makes my heart race...\nBut I'll be there cheering, no matter what!
You look like a culture club type...\nThey have a lot going for them,\nso I'm sure you'd have a great time.
Good job not cowering in front of <FLC:YAGYU>, of all people!\nYou're brave, that's for sure.
You're seriously using the old gym storage as your base?\nThat surely won't fly under the council's radar.
What position are you playing in the showdown?\nI'm hoping we get to see those killer dance moves again!
You didn't even take to the pitch?\nWait, so you're the coordinator,\nbut you don't actually play?!
<FLC:RAIKA> doesn't hold back, even against <FLC:SAKURAZAKI>...\nDon't go picking up any of their bad habits now, captain.
They're in a different building, so life's mostly the same.\nBut clubs are combined, and that's where the trouble always starts.
Hey, forgot something?\nI thought you'd be away for the whole tournament.
Royal Academy's well-disciplined. <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>?\nA bit messy. But hey, that's charm for ya!
I'm catching everyone's nerves. The whole school'll\nbe like this till the finals end.
Our uniforms look best when worn right:\nironed to perfection, tucked in, and buttoned up.
Your style is spot on!\nYou look stunning!
The eagle-eyed committee's quick to call out messy clothes,\nbut they never praise those who dress right.
<FLC:GOSAKI> leads the committee and the martial arts club.\nIf he catches you messing up, he'll send you flying.
That's a pretty bold way to break the uniform rules...\nWhere did you get that?
My whole life, I've lived on the straight and narrow,\nbut maybe I just don't have anything worth fighting back against yet...
You wouldn't have revived football by simply following the rules.\nMaybe sometimes you have to rebel.
Our headmaster doesn't seem like the type to yell at students.\nHe looks really kind. I wish we had more teachers like him.
Why on earth did you challenge the baseball club to\nthat-which-must-not-be-mentioned?! You know what I mean...
You guys... What you're doing is nuts.\nThere's no way you're actually going to create that club, right?
The football club's never coming back, no way!\nIf you break the rules, there'll be consequences...
The teachers were totally against it before,\nbut now they're supporting the football club?\nSomething smells fishy...
Miss <LST:KASUMISAKI>'s the football club advisor now. Not sure if I should\nbe impressed by your wits or grossed out by your grit, <FLC:UNMEI>...
This school has too many secrets.\nThey should share more info with us students.
There are tons of InaTubers spreading gossip about <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>.\nWe gotta crack down on them before it gets out of hand.
The key holders in the staff room aren't secure enough.\nCan't have people walking off with them willy-nilly.
People talk way\ntoo much in class.
I need to set\na good example.
You can tell nobody's really focused in class.\nI get it, though... It's the final, and I'm just as nervous!
I don't know, man. He's hard to read.\nMaybe he's super scary when he gets mad!
Wow, you're either brave or totally bonkers.\nChallenging the baseball club like that... Seriously, yikes.
You have to apply to the student council to start a club,\nbut I doubt they'd approve your application anytime soon.
Maybe merging the space lab and stargazing club is good.\nBigger clubs have more flexibility and benefits.
Being good with words\nreally is the key!
You'll find life difficult\nif you suck at math.
A global mindset is key\nin this day and age!
Just waiting for\nthe hammer to drop.
It'd be cool if she won.
What kind of trick\ndid they pull?
We'll have to make do with photos.
O, love of my heart!\nI am devout to thou!
Surely you jest! Why\ndost thou deny me so?
That drivel's all you've\nbeen spouting lately.
It seems your phone has\nyour undivided attention.
It has to be Kyushu's\nnumber one...
How dare thou intrude upon a moment betwixt fated lovers?!\nThou art a barbarian most uncouth!
There are but a wee six years left of our high school lives together.\nMy love, why dost thou shun mine own self?
Spring is the season of meetings, of partings, and of course, exams.\nDifficult questions coming and going,\none after another, in a dizzying vortex.
Uh, e-excuse me! I know my girlfriend is the cutest girl in the world,\nbut please don't kidnap her or anything!
When you think of top preparatory schools, West Manor comes to mind.\nBut if we're talking overall, our school's definitely far superior!
My girlfriend has an older sister that graduated from <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>.\nShe really wants to get into the same school as her...\nwouldn't that be great?!
Seems West Manor's coordinator is President <FLC:SENNO>'s little sister...\nBeating a rival team would normally be cause for celebration,\nbut she might have mixed feelings.
Northbright students had plenty of notice about the merger, huh?\nThey must be quite disciplined to have kept it under wraps this whole time!
My girlfriend has big ambitions. I'm happy for her, but it's led to\nour boyfriend-girlfriend time dropping to a bare minimum...
The football club's rising fast, just like the baseball club.\nYou guys are this year's dazzling dark horses.
Her thoughts seem drawn more and more to football...\nMaybe if I join the club, she'll see me differently and things will work out?
You'll have to forgive the poetic tendencies of my boyfriend...\nStill, he's a genius when it comes to guessing what the next test\nwill cover.
Considering how little time we have left,\nwe have to start preparing for our entrance exams.
While everyone's caught up in the football talk,\nI'm gonna hit the books hard and pull ahead.
I was dead set on <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>, so I enrolled in cram school—\nand that's where I met him.
I don't want to lose to anyone from West Manor on the next mock exam.\nI'll do whatever it takes to improve.
Thanks for beating West Manor.\nIt proves once again we're the better team.
Northbright's not a wild school, so the merger seems smooth so far.\nStill, all schools seem to be struggling these days...
If I want to get into a top university,\nI have to know where I stand nationally.
I don't know much about sports, but the tournament's still on.\nYou should wait until it's over before celebrating.
If you win, <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>'s reputation will soar.\nMaybe that's the way to go.
If they're up against\nthe baseball club...
We have a swimming club and a water polo club.\nDo be careful not to get them mixed up.
We're all talking about your beef with <FLC:YAGYU>.\nWhat were you thinking, doing something that reckless?
<FLC:KISOJI>'s a real social butterfly. He just walks up to anyone and\nstarts chatting... Must've been born that friendly!
Oh no, <FLC:KISOJI>'s one of your gofers now too?\nBe nice to him, okay?
I saw <FLC:KAMEO> in the shopping district, then, poof, and he was gone!\nIt wasn't a hallucination... I think.
<FLC:KOTEUCHI> totally stepped in and stopped those students from fighting.\nWe're all fans now!
The guys bullying <FLC:KAMEO>? They've been super quiet lately...\nAlmost like they're scared of something. Kinda spooky.
That guy from Northbright... <FLC:SORAMIYA>, right? Is he an old friend?\nYou two were talking like you've known each other forever.
I thought I saw <FUL:HARU> on campus, but no one believes me.\nHe's got no reason to be here, so maybe I was wrong.
Didn't you have a fight with <FLC:MANBE>? He's been all secretive lately.\nWhat's he up to?
Bet even the baseball guys are watching the football team.\nThey've been extra fired up lately too.
The library's on the\nthird floor, right...?
What kind of training\ndo they do...?
Let's try and get his\nattention again!
Why isn't there a football club?\nThis topic's off-limits, you know...\nBecause of an incident five years ago.
If only the football club hadn't gotten caught up in that mess...\nBecause of it, not just the club, but football itself got banned.
Can't believe they've\nmade it this far.
